Simpulum = ‘vas quo in sacrific-iis vinum libabatur': obba = ‘vas quo diis manibus vinum libabatur? ‘What is the difference,' Tertullian asks, ‘between a feast of Jupiter and a feast at an old man's funeral? between the sacrificial bowl and the vessel with which libations are made to the dead’? and sarcastically hints that the similarity of rites in both cases points to a similarity of present condition in the god and the mortal.
